summary: Sandra: But to your question of like, do we do anything to [build the tension between us]…I don’t know why we [talking to Jodie]...
body:
Sandra: But to your question of like, do we do anything to [build the tension between us]…I don’t know why we [talking to Jodie] get this question often. It’s not like, it’s not like we text each other or talk to each other or don’t talk to each other [Jodie agreeing in the background]. I think Jodie and I…Jodie and I just have a natural chemistry together and I think we listen to each other really well.

Jodie: Also, life kind of imitated art in the way that we were separated like the characters were, and then when we came to that scene where they meet for the first time -

Sandra: It was like finally. Let’s act together.

Jodie: Yeah, it was just as the moment was in real life and that’s just the way it kind of panned out.

Sandra: I mean, Eve is thinking about Villanelle…all the time. So, in a way, I am thinking about Jodie all the time as Villanelle. So it’s not like it’s something blank, you are actually focusing on that face.

summary: Are we not going to talk about Gabriel? He was such a sweet kid
question: Are we not going to talk about Gabriel? He was such a sweet kid
answer:
He was indeed a sweet kid. I think he just needed the help of therapy, both emotional and physical. Instead he had the worst luck and unknowingly confessed his sadness to someone who took his comments literally.

There are quite a few comments about him you might agree with in the ke tag. Most of which will eventually be in my fandom thoughts tag too :)

summary: It seems to be the same costume for these scenes. I’m wondering if it’s Villanelle’s mission for MI6 to disguise as a prostitute...
body:
Just curious about context of this costume.

It seems to be the same costume for these scenes. I’m wondering if it’s Villanelle’s mission for MI6 to disguise as a prostitute in a brothel to find out about human trafficking of The Twelve or the new female assassin.

I guess this will happen in 2x06 “I Hope You Like Missionary!” as the synopsis says “Villanelle uses her unrivaled infiltration skills to immerse herself in the world of a new target.”

Maybe the cry is just a fake again?



Anyone has any ideas you may want to share?

summary: "The mystery, and the woman at the heart of the mystery, speak to a part of Eve that she’s never really explored. Could she...
body:
“The mystery, and the woman at the heart of the mystery, speak to a part of Eve that she’s never really explored. Could she herself ever be transformed into someone who acts as her target does? Who kills without hesitation or pity? And if so, what would it take?”

Luke Jennings’ No Tomorrow
